# D365 F&O Core Standards

Microsoft source: [Extend F&O apps](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/guidance/implementation-guide/extend-your-solution-guidance-product-fo)

## Non-negotiables

- **Extensions only** — never overlayer (sealed models since v8.0)
- **Publisher prefix** on all new artifacts
- **Labels** (`@LabelId`) — no hardcoded user-facing strings
- Use `update()` / `insert()` / `delete()` — never `doUpdate()` / `doInsert()` / `doDelete()`
- Target **zero BP deviations**; run compatibility checker before release

## Scenarios and recommendations

### New customization in ISV/custom model

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Create artifacts in your publisher model only | Modify Microsoft sealed/base models in place |
| Name with publisher prefix (`MyPub_`) | Reuse `@SYS` labels or standard object names |
| Choose extension technique from hierarchy (metadata → CoC → events → plugin) | Jump to overlay because it is faster short-term |

### Upgrade / platform update incoming

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Run compatibility checker against last baseline | Change protected/public signatures without major version plan |
| Keep pack/unpack backward compatible for batch jobs | Remove fields from parameter containers without version branch |
| Duplicate standard security roles before editing | Edit standard `SecurityRole` artifacts |

### User-visible message or label change

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Add new label file entries (`@MyPubLabel:Key`) | Hardcode strings in X++ or form captions |
| Reference labels in `info`/`error`/`warning` | Modify existing Microsoft label IDs |

### Persisting table data from custom code

```xpp
// BAD — skips CoC, events, validation, security
custTable.doUpdate();

// GOOD
ttsbegin;
select forupdate custTable where custTable.AccountNum == _accountNum;
if (custTable)
{
    custTable.CreditMax = _amount;
    custTable.update();
}
ttscommit;
```

